I was running into similar difficulties with sharedFormulas and took me some time to figure it out. Hoping it might help, here's an explanation.

First, when writing the master formula, you need to include the **ref** and **sharetype** attributes.

The ref attributes must contain the range of cells that the master formula will be shared to. Note that any cell receiving the shared formula while not in this range will cause Excel issues and that you need to include the master formula's cell in the range for the same reason.
Sharetype is to separate array type from shared type formulas as mentioned in the docs.


Here, the fixing change would be :


```
// Master formula
sheet1.getCell('B1').value = { 
    formula: 'A1*2',
    ref: 'B1:B10',
    shareType: 'shared'
};
```
